{#
  ============================================================================
  TEMPLATE: procedure-eu_fsh.twig
  ============================================================================
  PURPOSE
    Generates a FSH Procedure instance conforming to the ProcedureEuCore
    profile. Each invocation represents a single clinical procedure performed
    on the patient, optionally qualified by a body site and a clinical reason.

  PROFILE CONFORMANCE
    InstanceOf: ProcedureEuCore
    Canonical : (EU Core Procedure profile, HL7 Europe)
    Must-support elements covered:
      status, code (SNOMED CT), performedDateTime (or absent-reason),
      reasonCode, bodySite, subject

  THREE-COLUMN HTML TABLE
    Column 1 — Procedure display name (+ optional body site on second line)
    Column 2 — Performed date  (conditional; "?" if absent)
    Column 3 — Reason code display (conditional; "-" if absent)

  NARRATIVE NOTE
    `emitHTML()` is flushed inside `text.div` so the inline FHIR narrative
    carries the data rows. However `emitHEAD()` is NOT called inside
    `text.div` — the narrative table therefore contains body rows only,
    without a column header row. The HEAD bag is emitted exclusively in the
    %%HEAD%% section for external consumers.

  PROCEDURE CODE DISPLAY — PREFERRED TERM + BODY SITE COMPOSITION
    The text shown in HTML td 1 is assembled in two steps:

      Step 1 — preferred term:
        `procedure.code.preferredTerm ?? procedure.code.display`
        The null-coalescing operator selects `preferredTerm` when available,
        falling back to `display`. This allows a locale-preferred SNOMED label
        to override the raw concept display string.

      Step 2 — body site suffix (conditional):
        When `procedure.site.code` is non-empty, the site display is appended
        with an HTML `<br/>` separator:
          "<preferred term><br/><site display>"
        This composite string is passed directly to `addHTML_td()`. The `<br/>`
        is rendered as a line break inside the HTML cell; it does NOT appear
        in the FSH output. The body site itself is also emitted separately as
        a `bodySite[+]` FSH rule.

  FSH CODE NOTATION
    This template uses explicit `[0]` indexing rather than the `[+]`/`[=]`
    pattern for `code.coding` and `reasonCode.coding`, since exactly one
    coding per element is expected:
      * code.coding[0]       = ...
      * reasonCode.coding[0] = ...

  PERFORMED DATE — ABSENT-REASON PATTERN
    When `procedure.date` is empty, a FHIR data-absent-reason extension is
    emitted on `performedDateTime` rather than omitting the element:
      * performedDateTime.extension.url       = ".../data-absent-reason"
      * performedDateTime.extension.valueCode = #unknown
    The HTML cell shows "?" to signal the gap to human readers.

  CONTEXT VARIABLES
  ┌──────────────────────────────┬──────────┬──────────────────────────────────────┐
  │ Variable                     │ Type     │ Description                          │
  ├──────────────────────────────┼──────────┼──────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ instanceid                   │ string   │ Unique resource id; appended to       │
  │                              │          │ "Instance-Procedure-" for the FSH    │
  │                              │          │ instance name.                       │
  │ patient.instanceid           │ string   │ UUID of the Patient resource for the  │
  │                              │          │ subject Reference.                   │
  │ patient.name                 │ string   │ Full display name for the subject     │
  │                              │          │ Reference display string.            │
  │ procedure.code               │ object?  │ Optional procedure code object.       │
  │   .system                    │ string   │   CodeSystem URI (e.g. SNOMED CT).   │
  │   .code                      │ string   │   Concept code.                      │
  │   .display                   │ string   │   Default display term.              │
  │   .preferredTerm             │ string?  │   Preferred display override; used   │
  │                              │          │   via ?? fallback to .display.       │
  │ procedure.date               │ string?  │ Optional ISO 8601 performedDateTime. │
  │                              │          │ When empty, data-absent-reason is    │
  │                              │          │ emitted instead.                     │
  │ procedure.reason             │ object?  │ Optional clinical reason object.     │
  │   .system                    │ string   │   CodeSystem URI.                    │
  │   .code                      │ string   │   Reason concept code (emptiness     │
  │                              │          │   tested via procedure.reason.code). │
  │   .display                   │ string   │   Reason display text.               │
  │ procedure.site               │ object?  │ Optional body site object.           │
  │   .system                    │ string   │   CodeSystem URI.                    │
  │   .code                      │ string   │   Site concept code (emptiness       │
  │                              │          │   tested to gate both HTML and FSH). │
  │   .display                   │ string   │   Site display text; appended to     │
  │                              │          │   td 1 after a `<br/>` separator.    │
  └──────────────────────────────┴──────────┴──────────────────────────────────────┘

  FSH ELEMENTS EMITTED
    * status                       always #completed
    * code.coding[0]               procedure type (when code is present)
    * performedDateTime            ISO 8601 date (when present)
    * performedDateTime.extension  data-absent-reason (when date is absent)
    * reasonCode.coding[0]         clinical reason (when present)
    * bodySite[+].coding           body site (when site.code is present)
    * subject                      Reference to the patient

  CODESYSTEMS REFERENCED
    Procedure code, reason, and body site system URIs are caller-supplied
    via the respective object fields.

  AUTHOR   KH
  SINCE    2025-09-02
  ============================================================================
#}

%%FSH%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}

Instance: {{ setInstance("Instance-Procedure-" ~ instanceid) }}
InstanceOf: ProcedureEuCore
Title: "Procedure (EU Core)"
Description: "Procedure"
Usage: #inline

* id = "{{ instanceid }}"

{#
  ── HEAD bag: three-column table header ────────────────────────────────────
  Note: flushed only in %%HEAD%%, NOT inside text.div — the inline narrative
  carries body rows only (no headers). See "Narrative Note" in the header.
#}
{{ addHEAD_tr() }}
{{ addHEAD_th("Procedure") }}
{{ addHEAD_th("Date") }}
{{ addHEAD_th("Reason") }}
{{ addHEAD_trend() -}}

{{ addHTML_tr() }}

{#
  ── Fixed status ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  All synthetic procedures are marked as completed.
#}
* status = #completed

{#
  ── Procedure code (td 1: conditional) ──────────────────────────────────────
  When code is present:
    - FSH: code.coding[0] with system, code, display (explicit [0] index;
           exactly one coding per procedure code is expected).
    - HTML: preferred term resolved via ?? operator, with optional body site
            appended as a second line using a raw <br/> HTML tag.
  When code is absent: HTML cell shows "-", no FSH rule emitted.
#}
{% if procedure.code is not empty %}
* code.coding[0] = {{ procedure.code.system }}#{{ procedure.code.code }} "{{ procedure.code.display }}"
{# Resolve display: preferredTerm overrides display when available #}
{% set dp = procedure.code.preferredTerm ?? procedure.code.display %}
{# Append body site display as a second line when site data is present #}
{% if procedure.site.code is not empty %}
{% set dp = dp ~ "<br/>" ~ procedure.site.display %}
{% endif %}
{{ addHTML_td(dp) }}
{% else %}
{{ addHTML_td("-") }}
{% endif %}

{#
  ── Performed date (td 2: conditional) ─────────────────────────────────────
  When date is absent: emit a data-absent-reason extension on performedDateTime
  (FHIR R4 pattern for unknown dates); HTML cell shows "?".
  When date is present: emit the ISO 8601 string in FSH; show formatted
  d-M-Y date (e.g. "14-Mar-1978") as a pill badge in the HTML cell.
#}
{% if procedure.date is empty %}
* performedDateTime.extension.url = "http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/data-absent-reason"
* performedDateTime.extension.valueCode = #unknown
{{ addHTML_td("?") }}
{% else %}
* performedDateTime = "{{ procedure.date }}"
{{ addHTML_tdnb(procedure.date|date('d-M-Y')) }}
{% endif %}

{#
  ── Reason code (td 3: conditional) ────────────────────────────────────────
  Conditioned on procedure.reason.code (the code sub-field, not reason itself)
  being non-empty. FSH uses explicit [0] index; one reason coding per procedure.
  HTML cell shows the display text as a plain cell (not a pill badge).
#}
{% if procedure.reason.code is empty %}
{{ addHTML_td("-") }}
{% else %}
* reasonCode.coding[0] = {{ procedure.reason.system }}#{{ procedure.reason.code }} "{{ procedure.reason.display }}"
{{ addHTML_td(procedure.reason.display) }}
{% endif %}

{#
  ── Body site (FSH only, no additional HTML cell) ───────────────────────────
  When site.code is non-empty, a bodySite[+] coding rule is emitted. The site
  display is already incorporated into td 1 above (as a <br/>-separated suffix
  on the procedure cell), so no additional HTML cell is produced here.
#}
{% if procedure.site.code is not empty %}
* bodySite[+].coding = {{ procedure.site.system }}#{{ procedure.site.code }} "{{ procedure.site.display }}"
{% endif %}

{#
  ── Patient reference ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#}
* subject = Reference(urn:uuid:{{ patient.instanceid }}) "{{ patient.name }}"

{{ addHTML_trend() -}}

{#
  ── FHIR narrative ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Only emitHTML() is called here — no emitHEAD(). The narrative table
  therefore contains data rows only, without column headers.
#}
* text.status = #generated
* text.div = """
<div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
<table class="hl7__ips">{{ emitHTML() | raw }}</table>
</div>
"""

%%HEAD%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}
{{ emitHEAD() | raw }}

%%HTML%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}
{{ emitHTML() | raw }}
